Symbolic Mathematics in Python with SymPy
=========================================

This module introduces the cyberinfrastructure skills of performing symbolic
mathematics in Python using the SymPy library.

#### Module Contents

<div><div><h2>Introduction to Symbolic Algebra in Python</h2><p>The purpose of this lesson is to help students develop foundational skills for performing symbolic algebra in Python using the <code>sympy</code> and <code>algebra_with_sympy</code> libraries (below, referred to collectively as SymPy), with some brief applications to problem solving at the general chemistry (first-year) level.</p><h2>Lesson Learning Outcomes (LOs)</h2><p>At the end of this lesson, students will be able to...</p><h3>Cyberinfrastructure LOs</h3><ol>
<li>
<p>Define mathematical variables and expressions using SymPy</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Manipulate algebraic expressions to solve for a single variable</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Substitute numerical values and units into algebraic expressions</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apply symbolic algebra techniques in Python to solve general chemistry problems</p>
</li>
</ol><h2>Lesson Prerequsites</h2><h3>CI Prereqs</h3><ul>
<li>
<p><a href="../python-basics/python-syntax.ipynb">Basic Python Syntax</a></p>
</li>
</ul><h3>Content Prereqs</h3><p>Students are expected to have a basic familiarity with the following concepts from first-year general chemistry:</p><ul>
<li>
<p>Gas Laws</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Thermochemistry</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Chemical Kinetics</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Chemical Equilibrium</p>
</li>
</ul><h2>Resources</h2><h3>Related Lessons</h3><ul>
