<li>
<p><a href="https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3">OpenStax Calculus Volume 3</a></p>
</li>
</ul></div><div><h2>Symbolic Representation of Operators in SymPy</h2><p>The purpose of this lesson is to help students develop the skill of symbolically applying mathematical operators to scalar functions using SymPy.</p><h2>Lesson Learning Outcomes (LOs)</h2><p>At the end of this lesson, students will be able to...</p><h3>Cyberinfrastructure LOs</h3><ol>
<li>
<p>Construct the SymPy representation of an operator from its mathematical definition,</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apply linear and nonlinear operators to definite SymPy expressions,</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Apply linear and nonlinear operators to arbitrary SymPy functions,</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Evaluate relationships of mathematical equality and inequality between SymPy expressions</p>
</li>
</ol><h2>Lesson Prerequsites</h2><h3>CI Prereqs</h3><ul>
